    <sTitle>Thermochemistry of hydrated ammonium borates</sTitle>
    <sAbstract>The enthalpies of solution of (NH4)2B4O7*4H2O (cr) and NH4B5O8*4H2O (cr) in approximately 1 mol dm-3 aqueous hydrochloric acid solution, as well as the enthalpy of solution of NH4Cl (cr) in aqueous (hydrochloric acid + boric acid) have been measured by using a microcalorimeter. From these results and other auxiliary data, the standard molar enthalpies of formation ?fH0m of (NH4)2B4O7*4H2O (cr) and NH4B5O8*4H2O (cr) have been derived to be (-4313.74 +- 3.26) and (-4703.56 +- 4.03) kJ mol-1 at 298.15 K, respectively. Some other thermodynamic properties of the title borates, such as the standard molar entropies of formation and the standard molar entropies have also been calculated.</sAbstract>
